Install WordPress:

Visit WordPress.org and download the latest version.
Follow the installation instructions to set up WordPress on your server.
Log in to WordPress Dashboard:

Access your WordPress admin dashboard (typically located at http://yourdomain.com/wp-admin/).
Create a New Post:

Go to Posts -> Add New to create a new blog post.
In the editor, you can use HTML tags directly. For example:
<h2>This is a Blog Post Title</h2>
<p>This is a paragraph of text in the blog post.</p>
<a href="https://example.com">Visit Example.com</a>
Anchor Tag (Link):
Use the <a> tag for anchor tags. Example:
<a href="https://example.com">Visit Example.com</a>
Title Tag:
WordPress automatically generates title tags based on your post title. Ensure your post title is descriptive and relevant.

Publish Your Post:
Once you've added your content, click the "Publish" button to make your post live.

View Your Blog:
Visit your blog's main page to see your new post
